abstract: >-
  TreeBench is a benchmark of 861 questions designed to expose structural
  evidence failures in retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) over hierarchically
  structured corpora. It targets structural confounder pairs -- nodes that are
  semantically similar but structurally incompatible -- across 5 regulatory
  domains and 10 failure types.
